# Trawl local anonymization patterns (COPY TO `anonymize.local.toml`)
#
# This file lets you anonymize content that contains personal details
# specific to you or your collaborators. The real file must be GITIGNORED
# so that personal patterns never enter source control.
#
# Format: one rule per line, `<regex> -> <replacement>`
# Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Replacement placeholders (resolved per-entry from random pools):
#   {name}         — a random name from NAMES (Alice, Bob, ...)
#   {city}         — a random city from CITIES (Tokyo, Berlin, ...)
#   {nationality}  — a random nationality from NATIONALITIES
#   {language}     — a random language from LANGUAGES
#
# Setup:
#   1. cp anonymize.local.toml.example anonymize.local.toml
#   2. Add your own patterns below (do NOT commit the copy)
#   3. Run trawl — patterns load from the file automatically

# Example (delete these and add your own):
# \bAlex Example\b -> {name}
# (?i)near Springfield -> near {city}
# (?i)\bExamplelander\b -> {nationality}
